This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their application in image classification and patch matching. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the learning process of CNNs. Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the ability of CNNs to learn and exploit spatial location information. Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the use of CNNs in video classification.
